So in case of TestNet, you can check which SVs have already whitelisted you by running this command
```for url in $(curl -sS <https://scan.sv-1.test.global.canton.network.sync.global/api/scan/v0/scans> | jq -r '.scans[].scans[].publicUrl' ); do
  result=$( { curl -sf --max-time 5 "$url/api/scan/version" || echo '{}'; } | jq -r '.version // "error"');
  echo "$url: $result";
done```

